archive:
    play sound click
    choice:
        "The Sinner is foraging for something in the city archive."
        "[Find out what The Sinner is up to] <span class='prompt'>[[-1 ACTION]]</span>" if (>= $stats.actions.value 1):
            play sound spendAction
            set data.game_map.inMap false
            add_stat actions -1
            set_button button_archive false
            run transition_black archive_ext
            clear_dialog
        "<span class='prompt'>[[BACK]]</span>":
            jump game_map

    "The Sinner leans against the facade of the City Archive, smoking and buttressing the building up. She's been waiting for you."
    if (roll archive_wait_orb orb 60):
        talk orb talk "She fucked up the time and arrived two hours early and has been trying really hard to look like she planned to stand here for so long because the archives receptionist keeps staring at her." 
        clear_dialog
    "She hasn't noticed you yet, granting you the rare opportunity to observe her naturalistically."
    choice:
        "She's so tall it's silly. A gnarled tree too stubborn to be uprooted. She blows out a billow of smoke and drops her cigarette to the ground, crushing it with her boot, which adds an additional two inches to her already terrifying height. The poor cigarette is obliterated."
        "[Tap a stranger on the shoulder] \\"I'd find that really horny if I was into feet, which I'm not.\\"":
            set data.ghost.footGirl true
            "The stranger doesn't know what <span class='writtenText'>'that'</span> is referring to, but rightfully hurries away without so much as glancing at you."
        "[Tap a stranger on the shoulder] \\"I wish I was getting stepped on and pulverised by a tall transexual wearing two inch thick boots. Wowie!\\"":
            set data.ghost.footGirl true
            "The stranger doesn't know what have prompted this, and rightfully hurries away without so much as glancing at you."
        "[Resist the urge to say anything weird to anyone]":
            run skip
    clear_dialog 
    choice:
        "The Sinner checks her watch. Yup, still doesn't have one. She sighs, and her shoulders slump a little further."
        "[Approach her before she looks even sadder] \\"Hello! It's me!\\" [Look incredibly serious for a moment] \\"You're so tall.\\"":
            run transition archive_ext_ghost
            "The Sinner hears you before you even speak. You have a recognisable stumble."
            clear_dialog
            talk sinner talk "Ah, I am, aren't I?"
            if (roll archive_blush_lovely lovely 40):
                talk lovely talk "She physically held back a blush. She enjoys her height. Enjoys the effect it has on women."
            else:
                wait 1000
    clear_dialog
    "The Sinner stops leaning on the wall, becoming slightly taller, and heads to the Archive door."
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        talk sinner talk "Come, let us march ever onwards..."
        "[Follow her inside]":
            play sound footstepsinside
            run transition archive_int
            clear_dialog
            choice:
                "The archive is dusty. Not many people come here, and the council doesn't have enough budget to actually hire anyone to keep it orderly. All of the council tax is spent on keeping the train station and the replacement bus service station as gentrified as possible."
                "\\"What are we doing in the town archive?\\"":
                    choice:
                        talk sinner talk "I will bathe in <span class='magenta'>magenta</span> and drown in it. And when it ends, it ends for good. I will be free, Ghost."
                        "[Nod]":
                            choice:
                                talk sinner talk "That is why we're here, Ghost. To find the cave."
                                "\\"Right of course, I should have realised that. What cave?\\"":
                                    run skip
                        "Gang, what is this woman trying to say?":
                            talk orb talk "She doesn't want this to happen anymore. This being *everything*."
                            talk orb talk "She's tired, Ghost. The world is too cruel for some women."
                            clear_dialog
                            choice:
                                talk sinner talk "That is why we're here, Ghost. To find the cave."
                                "\\"Right of course, I should have realised that. What cave.\\"":
                                    run skip
    clear_dialog
    talk sinner talk "The cards have made a promise to me, Ghost. CCLXII... LXXVIII... CI... VII... these signs keep coming up..."
    clear_dialog
    talk orb talk "In case you're not following: She's been convinced by her cards there's a cave in the woods that will lead her to The Cloud Sea. To The Seventh, where her soul will dissipate and she will finally be free. All she has to do is let herself plunge."
    talk nasty talk "Deranged. She's so sexy."
    clear_dialog
    talk sinner talk "I've been receiving the same reading for months now. For as long as my nights have been haunted by the dream..."
    talk sinner talk "CCLXII: The Stain. Unescapable, uncleanable sin. Guilt. Regret. Doom."
    talk sinner talk "LXXVIII: The Pale Spectre. A dying woman. Spiritual or physical decline."
    talk sinner talk "CI: The Cave. Escape. Hiding. The path through."
    clear_dialog
    "She shivers."
    clear_dialog
    play music magenta
    run transition magenta
    talk sinner talk "And The Seventh."
    talk sinner talk "Every time. The Seventh City. Escape... salvation... mercy... obliteration in <span class='magenta'>magenta</span>..."
    clear_dialog
    talk sinner talk "My only hope for absolution. Most likely yours too."
    clear_dialog
    "The Sinner leans into you. You feel her breath on you. Her eyes are manic, you sink into them."
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        talk sinner talk "Tell me, Ghost, will you walk with me into <span class='magenta'>magenta</span>?"
        "\\"I am undecided on walking into <span class='magenta'>magenta</span>. I'm not entirely sure what that even means.\\"":
            talk sinner talk "Freedom, Ghost. Freedom from this awful world."
        "\\"You think you can just walk there from here? With your feet?\\"":
            if (roll archive_feet_nasty nasty 20):
                talk nasty talk "Feet."
                clear_dialog
            talk sinner talk "I do. I have to. I must. It is what has to happen."
            if (roll archive_repetition_orb orb 40):
                talk orb talk "Repetition makes you seem more resolute. You sound more correct if you repeat your statements several times. If you say the same thing a lot, people believe you."
                talk nasty talk "Great point, Orb, you're so smart."
                talk lovely talk "Orb is right, I think!"
                talk nasty talk "Great point, Orb, you're so smart."
            else:
                wait 1000
            clear_dialog
            talk sinner talk "I must march, without fear, and in full acceptance of all that I have done, through the gates. And then I will be free."
        "\\"Are you asking me to jump into a cave and die with you?\\"":
            talk sinner talk "<span class='magenta'>magenta</span> is not death, Ghost, it is salvation. Sidestepping the eternal torment of The Void or The Divine, fleeing instead into the silken calm of oblivion."
            talk sinner talk "This world is not so good as to be worth clinging to."
    clear_dialog
    stop music
    play music intro
    run transition archive_int
    "A grim silence settles over her."
    clear_dialog
    talk sinner talk "I need a smoke."
    clear_dialog
    play sound footstepsinside
    run transition archive_int_alone
    "She strides away from you, lighting another oestradiol cigarette. Her minty smell lingers on. It's like she never left."
    clear_dialog
    talk lovely talk "Oh! Rude!"
    talk orb talk "She'll be back. She's just being dramatic again. Also she's addicted to smoking and drugs."
    talk nasty talk "Come now Orb, <span class='writtenText'>addicted'</span> is such an ugly word... I prefer to think of it as being locked in a dangerous, illicit, but oh so sexually charged affair..."
    clear_dialog
    if $data.apartment.orbKnows:
        choice:
            talk orb talk "This woman sits there every night intentionally pulling out the four cards she knows will make her feel bad, because it makes her feel *something*, and has brainwormed herself into forgetting she's doing it on purpose and making self-obliteration her goal. It's sad. You shouldn't encourage her, Ghost."
            "I'll try, she seems a little far gone though.":
                talk orb talk "It's all you can do."
            "[Shrug] Picking at scabs can be cathartic.":
                talk orb talk "Not when it ends up killing you. Not if picking scabs could unmake you."
    jump archive_menu

archive_menu:
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        "The Sinner has not yet returned from her tizzy."
        "[Look around the archive]":
            "A somewhat grim room. The corners are more cobweb than geometry. Every single book is coated in dust."
            clear_dialog
            talk orb talk "The archive has seen better days. Unfortunately the city has been underfunding it for some time. Tory cuts."
            talk nasty talk "*Cunts."
            clear_dialog
            "The receptionist occasionally gives you a dirty look (though this may just be because you keep staring at her, and because The Sinner keeps stubbing her cigarettes out on the books)."
            if (roll archive_menu_tranny_nightmare nightmare 40):
                talk nightmare talk "<span class='nightmare'>you know why she's giving u a dirty look. tranny.</span>"
            else:
                wait 1000
            jump archive_menu
        "[Poke through one of the bookcases for anything interesting]":
            if $data.archive.bookcaseSearched:
                "There's nothing interesting."
            else:
                set data.archive.bookcaseSearched true
                "There's nothing interesting, but you do find a penny hidden behind a copy of <span class='writtenText'>'THAMES VALLEY BUILDING REGULATIONS: 1923 EDITION'</span>, so that's cool."
                add_stat money 1
                play sound coins
            jump archive_menu
        "[Twiddle your thumbs]":
            "Somehow you end up twaddling your thumbs instead. Embarrassing."
            jump archive_menu
        "[Stand silently and wait for The Sinner to return] <span class='prompt'>[[MOVE ON]]</span>":
            wait 4000
            jump archive_return

archive_return:
    play sound footstepsinside
    run transition archive_int
    "The Sinner bursts back into the room."
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        talk sinner talk "I'm back."
        "\\"She's back!\\"":
            talk sinner talk "I am."
            clear_dialog
            "She lights a cigarette. The receptionist rolls her eyes, sighs and slumps forward with her head in her hands."
            clear_dialog
            talk sinner talk "Will you join me on this journey, Ghost?"
    jump archive_sinner_menu

archive_sinner_menu:
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        "The Sinner squints at you."
        "\\"So why do you want to jump down this cave so badly? Is it fun? Is there a slide or something?\\"":
            choice:
                talk sinner talk "I don't want to <span class='writtenText'>'jump down a cave'</span>. And certainly not for *fun*. The cave serves merely as a transitory passage between this, the sleeping world, and there, the world of The Dreamer."
                "[Nod] \\"Of course. Of course. Is it fun though? You never said if there would be a slide or not and whether or not I come along is kind of riding on that, to be honest.\\"":
                    talk sinner talk "No. No slide."
                    clear_dialog
                    "She thinks."
                    clear_dialog
                    talk sinner talk "Or maybe yes. Come along and we'll find out, hmm?"
            jump archive_sinner_menu
        "\\"I'm not convinced the world is *that* bad. I'm kind of enjoying it, honestly. Name *one* thing I should feel bad about.\\"":
            "The Sinner shrugs."
            clear_dialog
            talk sinner talk "I can name many <span class='writtenText'>'bad things'</span>."
            jump archive_sinner_menu
        "\\"I'm undecided about hurling myself into the depths on a quest to unmake my soul, but I'd like to hang out with you some more so sure, I'll come along on your little quest.\\" <span class='prompt'>[[MOVE ON]]</span>":
            "The Sinner doesn't seem particularly impressed with your answer, but it wasn't a <span class='writtenText'>'get help'</span>, at least. She's used to that."
            jump archive_sinner
        "\\"The world does seem pretty sad and bad, maybe not ever have having lived would be better for me?\\" <span class='prompt'>[[MOVE ON]]</span>":
            "The Sinner smiles. Vindication."
            jump archive_sinner

archive_sinner:
    clear_dialog
    talk sinner talk "You know, Ghost, usually people try to stop me from finding salvation, they call it self-destruction, madness."
    talk sinner talk "But it is as Elasia said: <span class='writtenText'>'Let no messy wenches and thy flair for drama distract me from thy course.'</span>"
    if (roll archive_messy_nasty nasty 20):
        talk nasty talk "She's saying she won't let messy bitches who love drama distract her from her sheepshit."
    talk lovely talk "Pardon me for saying this, but methinks The Sinner is hardly one to chastise others for their flair for drama."
    if (roll archive_diary_orb orb 40):
        run transition diary
        talk orb talk "It's a quote from <span class='writtenText'>'Il diario dell'oro sacro'</span>, the closest thing the Anglian church has to a holy book."
        talk orb talk "Dawnsights diary. It has a heart shaped padlock on it, is pink, and has <span class='writtenText'>'Thine Girlish Secrets'</span> written on the cover."
        clear_dialog
        talk lovely talk "She bequeathed it upon us when she departed our chalky shores that it might guide us in her absence."
        if (roll archive_forgot_orb orb 60):
            talk orb talk "No. She just forgot to take it with her."
        else:
            wait 1000
        clear_dialog
    else:
        wait 1000
    run transition archive_int_book
    clear_dialog
    "The Sinner pulls a book from the shelf. The <span class='writtenText'>'1846 Cave Census'</span>."
    "A plume of dust engulfs you. It has not been removed from the shelf for a long time."
    "She blows across the cover. A plume of dust engulfs you. It has not been looked at for a long time."
    play sound pageturn
    "The Sinner opens it up. A plume of dust engulfs you."
    clear_dialog
    "The Sinner begins scanning through the tome."
    clear_dialog
    talk sinner talk "The Cave Census... I've been looking for this for weeks..."
    if (roll archive_census_orb orb 20):
        talk orb talk "Bluehills has a weird history of doing censuses for basically everything. Barrows. Caves. Bats."
        talk orb talk "They once did a <span class='writtenText'>'gnome census'</span>, but left behind no explanation of what that meant. All we know is they *apparently* found five gnomes."
        if (roll archive_nikita_orb orb 40):
            talk orb talk "It sits on one of the shelves here, untouched, from 1932 to 2023, when someone called <span class='nikita'>Nikita</span> steals it for <span class='nikitaQuote'>'vital and integral gnome and being research, you wouldn't understand, Smith'</span>."
        else:
            wait 1000
    else:
        wait 1000
    clear_dialog
    play music magenta
    talk sinner talk "Some escape to the other cities, crawling like lice on the angels, but no... I won't be like them, no no, there is only oblivion awaiting... one cannot have sinned if one never lived."
    talk sinner talk "To sink into <span class='magenta'>magenta</span> is to be undreamed. It is freedom, Ghost. There will be no Third Sinking, no deluge to punish us, we must make our own..."
    clear_dialog
    "The Sinner kind of mumbles incoherently."
    if (roll archive_sleepy_lovely lovely 60):
        talk lovely talk "She's half asleep. She didn't sleep well, again. She kept going over the conversations he had with you in her head, beating herself up about it. <span class='writtenText'>'Why didn't she want to stay with me last night?'</span>, she wonders."
    else:
        wait 1000
    clear_dialog
    set data.ghost.knowsDreamer true
    choice:
        talk sinner talk "Past the fall of heaven. Past the Endzeit, the day the dreamer awakens. Past the writhing. No. This world is not worth that. For me, Ghost, only <span class='magenta'>magenta</span> calls."
        "\\"Cool.\\"":
            "The Sinner seems to notice something. A fleeting glimpse of <span class='magenta'>magenta</span> in your iris..."
        "\\"Cool?\\"":
            "The Sinner seems to notice something. A fleeting glimpse of <span class='magenta'>magenta</span> in your iris..."
        "\\"Oh. Sorry to hear that, I think? I didn't really understand.\\"":
            "The Sinner seems to notice something. A fleeting glimpse of <span class='magenta'>magenta</span> in your iris..."
        "\\"Same.\\"":
            "The Sinner seems to notice something. A fleeting glimpse of <span class='magenta'>magenta</span> in your iris..."
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        talk sinner talk "You've seen it too, haven't you, Ghost. The shining city in the clouds."
        "\\"<span class='magenta'>magenta</span>\\"":
            play ambient magenta_two 1
            choice:
                talk sinner talk "So I ask you, that we might walk, together, into its light. Do you too seek to return? To no longer play your part in this grim facade."
                "[Scratch your wrist a little bit too hard] \\"More than anything. More than anything...\\"":
                    talk sinner talk "Walk with me tomorrow, Ghost. In the woods. We'll find it together. We'll both leave this all behind. We'll finally be free."
                    clear_dialog
                    "There is a tear running down her cheek. You're the first person she's met to which *it* calls."
                "\\"I don't know. I don't know...\\"":
                    "She swallows something. Some emotion or other."
                    clear_dialog
                    talk sinner talk "Nor do I. Nor do I..."
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        talk orb talk "Are you okay Ghost? You're sounding weirder than normal."
        "[Shake it off] I'm okay. I'm not sure what came over me.":
            "<span class='magenta'>magenta</span>"
    clear_dialog
    stop music
    stop ambient 1
    "The Archive is silent. Your ears seem to pop. Your body feels all too present. Passed from a pocket reality consisting solely of yourself and The Sinner, back into reality."
    clear_dialog
    talk sinner talk "Pah. Nothing. The records do not speak of the cave I seek... nothing matches my dreams..."
    clear_dialog
    play sound thud
    "She tosses the dusty old book into your hands, dust billows across your face."
    clear_dialog
    talk sinner talk "Truly we were put on this rock only to suffer with no hope for salvation... I'm going home and never trudging outside again..."
    run transition archive_int_read
    jump archive_book_menu

archive_book_menu:
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        "The 1846 Cave Census is heavy. Your poor little arms tremble from its weight."
        "[Open the book]" if (!= $data.archive.bookOpen true):
            set data.archive.bookOpen true
            play sound pageturn
            "You open the book. There's no dust left, but it's too late, you already look like you've just survived an incendiary attack."
            "The book consists almost entirely of a single hundred-page long table detailing caves, their names, locations and (in a few lucky cases) brief description of them. It's all pretty mundane, but a few names stand out to you."
            clear_dialog
            talk nasty talk "This looks really fucking boring."
            jump archive_book_menu
        "[Look at the entry for <span class='writtenText'>'Mossthistle Cave'</span>]" if $data.archive.bookOpen:
            play sound pageturn
            "<span class='writtenText'>'Mossthistle Cave'</span>"
            "<span class='writtenText'>'Grid Reference: 76, 20'</span>"
            "<span class='writtenText'>'Rumored resting place of Mossthistle clan members, but name may also come from unusual moss found inside.'</span>"
            if (roll archive_book_menu_moss_orb orb 40):
                talk orb talk "It's from the moss, sadly. I wish the more interesting answer could always be true, but it's often not. Life is cruel."
            else:
                wait 1000
            jump archive_book_menu
        "[Look at the entry for <span class='writtenText'>'Scarry Cave'</span>]" if $data.archive.bookOpen:
            play sound pageturn
            "<span class='writtenText'>'Scarry Cave'</span>"
            "<span class='writtenText'>'Grid Reference: 6, scribble'</span>"
            "<span class='writtenText'>'Oouuuahhh! Vewwy vewwy scarry!'</span>"
            if (roll archive_book_menu_work_orb orb 40):
                talk orb talk "Bring your daughter to work day was a disaster for the census office."
            else:
                wait 1000
            jump archive_book_menu
        "[Look at the entry for <span class='writtenText'>'Boring Cave, Not Worth Visiting'</span>]" if $data.archive.bookOpen:
            play sound pageturn
            "<span class='writtenText'>'Boring Cave, Not Worth Visiting'</span>"
            "<span class='writtenText'>'Grid Reference: REDACTED'</span>"
            "<span class='writtenText'>'Boring Cave, Not Worth Visiting'</span>"
            if (roll archive_book_menu_cave_orb orb 90):
                talk orb talk "Categorically *not* a boring cave, despite what this book wants you to believe. It's one of the few 'artery caves' leading to the Slumbering Hive."
                talk orb talk "An intrepid enough adventurer could find their way down there and stumble upon wonders beyond their wildest imaginations. The sleeping subterranean Mantis empire."
                talk orb talk "It's likely whoever discovered it realised this and quickly covered it up."
                clear_dialog
                talk orb talk "Hopefully they also returned and filled the cave with concrete. The last thing you surface dwellers need is to piss off the hive for the third time, and have even more of your little world sink into the depths."
                choice:
                    talk orb talk "Maybe you'll be lucky and only Anglia will crumble? Maybe not. The alps are a load bearing mountain range. They go the rest of the planets landmass goes with them."
                    "Why would you tell me this? That's awful. Our entire lives are literally held up on the whims of literal bugs. *Literal* bugs. They could kill us all right this moment, if they wanted. I think I might develop an unhealthy coping mechanism or two to deal with this. Alcoholism or eating grass maybe. Perhaps The Sinner is right? Perhaps <span class='magenta'>magenta</span> is the better fate?":
                        run skip
            else:
                wait 1000
            jump archive_book_menu
        "[Look at the entry for <span class='writtenText'>'Bloodlake Cave'</span>]" if $data.archive.bookOpen:
            play sound pageturn
            "<span class='writtenText'>'Bloodlake Cave'</span>"
            "<span class='writtenText'>'Grid Reference: 62, 38'</span>"
            "<span class='writtenText'>'Historial (likely Dark Age) sacrificial site. Pending study.'</span>"
            if (roll archive_book_menu_study_orb orb 60):
                talk orb talk "The cave *is* studied, eventually. It confirmed the suspicions, the cave used to be flooded in blood. Brown residue still clings to the rocks. Sacrifices from nearby settlements were performed here in the hope of bringing forth food when the ash blocked the sun."
                talk orb talk "Dawnsights salvation was too slow for some."
            else:
                wait 1000
            jump archive_book_menu
        "[Put the book back on its shelf] <span class='prompt'>[[MOVE ON]]</span>":
            play sound bookdown
            jump archive_end

archive_end:
    run transition archive_int
    "The Sinner has slumped against a bookcase. She looks tired. Moreso than normal."
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        talk sinner talk "This world is too evil, Ghost... I hate it... I hate that I was born here..."
        "\\"I have a suggestion: Going outside and taking a walk. It's good for you.\\" [Nod] \\"Who knows, maybe we'll even find your cave!\\"":
            "The Sinner reacts to the phrase <span class='writtenText'>'going outside and taking a walk. It's good for you'</span> in the same way one might react to <span class='writtenText'>'hey can I fuck your sister?'</span>."
            clear_dialog
            talk sinner talk "Outside. Walk."
            clear_dialog
            choice:
                "She turns the words about in her mouth as if she's uncertain they're edible."
                "[Nod] \\"The woods outside my cottage are oh so pretty, and I when I'm sad I always like to take a stroll. It makes me feel better. My point is you seem sad.\\" <span class='prompt'>[[CONTINUE]]</span>":
                    play sound spendAction
                    talk sinner talk "Sad? Pah. No."
                    clear_dialog
                    "She sighs."
                    clear_dialog
                    talk sinner talk "But fine. A walk. Tomorrow morning. Be there or... don't I guess."
                    complete_objective sinner archive
                    start_objective sinner woods
                    jump goToGameMap